  "compatibility_policy": [
    "Existing student-facing fields may not be deleted or repurposed.",
    "New optional fields may be added when the schema contract version is incremented.",
    "route_decision is additive and distinguishes select, clarify, and unsupported without changing legacy answer fields.",
    "Legacy solvers continue to consume knowns, flags, and requested_outputs through the v1 compatibility view.",
    "AnswerItem output_key disambiguates colliding display symbols without removing legacy symbol or label fields.",
    "Clarification input_fields adds typed multi-value inputs while needs_value remains for single-value clients.",
    "selection_decision is an additive Phase 47 diagnostic; legacy answer and verification fields remain authoritative compatibility views.",
    "structured_checks and policy_version are additive Phase 48 verification evidence; legacy checks, warnings, and errors remain compatibility views.",
    "explanation_evidence and explanation_trace are additive Phase 53 provenance views; existing answer fields and the result gate remain authoritative."
  ]
